
[1]hypocrite

   HYP'OCRITE, n.

   1. One who feigns to be what he is not; one who has the form of
   godliness without the power, or who assumes an appearance of piety and
   virtue, when he is destitute of true religion.

   And the hypocrite's hope shall perish. Job.8.

   2. A dissembler; one who assumes a false appearance.

   Fair hypocrite, you seek to cheat in vain.
